                    "value": "<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A living creature ends its turn in area A11 at night;</p>\n<p><strong>Effect</strong> A ghastly image of Belcorra, seemingly composed of fresh blood, rises from the bloodstain on the floor and rotates in place like a lighthouse. Beams of cold blue light shine from Belcorra&rsquo;s eyes and open mouth, causing blisters and decay to spread across flesh. Living creatures within a 30-foot burst from the center of area A11 must attempt a DC 20 Fortitude save. The haunt then rolls initiative.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes [[/r 1d8 #negative]] negative damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes [[/r 1d8+6 #negative]] negative damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Dazzled]{Dazzled} for 1 round.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes [[/r 2d8+6 #negative]] negative damage and is @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Blinded]{Blinded} for 1 round then dazzled for 1 round.</p>"
